In the context of this Agreement, the term "Control Shift" denotes:

(A) The acquisition or transfer, singularly or collectively, of more than half of the outstanding voting shares of either a Party or its parent entity, by individuals or entities that did not hold a majority on the Effective Date;

(B) A reorganization, merger, or consolidation involving a Party or its parent entity, unless post-combination, the same group retains beneficial ownership, either directly or indirectly, of more than half of the voting shares of the surviving entity;

(C) The sale or disposal, singularly or collectively, of most assets belonging to a Party or its parent entity;

(D) Any other event that leads to the loss of control by the individuals or group controlling the Party or its parent on the Effective Date over the management and decision-making processes of such entity. For clarification, Bunker Holding Group is recognized as the parent company of Bunker One, Inc., while Vertex Energy, Inc. is acknowledged as the parent of Vertex Energy Operating LLC.

In this revised formulation, the original term "Change in Control" has been replaced with a more neutral term, "Control Shift", and the obligations have been slightly weakened to focus on the loss of control rather than the acquisition of it. This change should make the clause applicable to a broader range of situations while maintaining its professional and realistic nature.
